---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import BlogNavigation from "../components/landing/BlogNavigation.astro";
import Footer from "../components/landing/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/landing.css";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={`Privacy Policy | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
      description="Privacy Policy according to GDPR."
    />
    <style>
      .legal-page {
        padding-top: 4rem;
        background: #fff;
      }

      .legal-hero {
        padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgb(45 79 64 / 10%) 0%, rgb(248 249 241 / 65%) 100%);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(197 160 89 / 20%);
      }

      .legal-hero .eyebrow {
        color: var(--forest);
      }

      .legal-hero p {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        max-width: 44rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      .legal-content {
        padding: 3rem 0 6rem;
      }

      .legal-card {
        border: 1px solid rgb(197 160 89 / 25%);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        background: #fdfcfb;
        padding: 2rem;
      }

      .legal-card h2 {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        font-size: 1.35rem;
      }

      .legal-card h2:first-child {
        margin-top: 0;
      }

      .legal-card p,
      .legal-card li {
        margin-top: 0.75rem;
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.65;
      }

      .legal-card ul {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 0 1.2rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <BlogNavigation />
    <main class="legal-page">
      <section class="legal-hero">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
          <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-content">
        <div class="container">
          <article class="legal-card">
            <h2>1. Controller</h2>
            <p>
              The controller responsible for data processing on this website is:
            </p>
            <p>
              Sebastian Faber<br />
              Freiherr-vom-Stein Straße 386b<br />
              45133 Essen<br />
              Germany
            </p>
            <p>
              E-Mail: <a href="mailto:fabersebastian@proton.me">fabersebastian@proton.me</a>
            </p>

            <h2>2. Access data (server log files)</h2>
            <p>
              When this website is accessed, information is automatically collected by the hosting
              provider and stored in so-called server log files. This may include:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>IP address</li>
              <li>Date and time of the request</li>
              <li>Requested page / file</li>
              <li>Amount of data transferred</li>
              <li>Browser type and browser version</li>
              <li>Operating system</li>
              <li>Referrer URL</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              This data is used exclusively to ensure trouble-free operation of the website and to
              improve our offering.
            </p>
            <p>The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.</p>

            <h2>3. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              If you contact me by email, your details are stored for the purpose of processing your
              inquiry and for possible follow-up questions.
            </p>
            <p>This data will not be shared without your consent.</p>
            <p>
              The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (pre-contractual communication) and/or
              Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Your rights</h2>
            <p>
              Within the applicable legal framework, you have the right at any time to:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Access your stored personal data</li>
              <li>Rectify inaccurate data</li>
              <li>Delete your data</li>
              <li>Restrict processing</li>
              <li>Object to processing</li>
              <li>Data portability</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              To exercise these rights, you can contact the address listed above at any time.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2>
            <p>
              You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority
              regarding the processing of your personal data.
            </p>
            <p>
              A list of data protection authorities and their contact details can be found at:
              <br />
              <a
                href="https://www.bfdi.bund.de/DE/Service/Anschriften/anschriften_table.html"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                https://www.bfdi.bund.de/DE/Service/Anschriften/anschriften_table.html
              </a>
            </p>

            <h2>6. Changes to this privacy policy</h2>
            <p>
              This privacy policy may be updated to reflect current legal requirements or changes to
              our services.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
